1
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:18,280
Come on!

2
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:20,600
Where are we going?

3
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:23,920
Liu Liu, she's here!

4
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,680
Hurry up, get over there, come on!

5
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:38,720
Come on!

6
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:45,080
Liu Liu

7
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,760
We've known each other for so long

8
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:49,960
I think we know each other well enough

9
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:53,000
Would you take it one step further

10
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,000
and be my girlfriend?

11
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:23,480
Say yes! Say yes! Say yes!

12
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:42,320
Say yes! Say yes! Say yes!

13
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,160
Who is it?

14
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:45,280
Who? What do you mean?

15
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,760
Ever since I met you in first grade,

16
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,160
you've always been like this.

17
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:15,400
How have you not learned anything?

18
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,680
Can't you ever learn to say no?

19
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:20,440
I knew you'd show up, my hero.

20
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:24,920
Girl.

21
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,760
Did I save the wrong person?

22
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:29,000
Of course not.

23
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,000
Let me tell you,

24
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,400
if you hadn't come, I would've died of fright.

25
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,960
So if I really hadn't shown up,

26
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:40,480
would you have actually said yes to him?

27
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,760
Of course not.

28
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:44,680
But I thought,

29
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,960
with so many people standing there,

30
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,560
I couldn't be too blunt about it.

31
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,840
If I'd really turned him down,

32
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,720
he probably would've felt so embarrassed.

33
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,600
Girl, come on.

34
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,680
I give up on you.

35
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,240
Are you some kind of saint?

36
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,840
You think about everyone else.

37
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,640
Aren't you exhausted from worrying so much?

38
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,840
Maybe think about yourself once in a while,

39
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:07,520
okay?

40
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,880
Unbelievable.

41
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,800
But isn't being confessed to

42
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,240
such an amazing feeling?

43
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:44,720
Ms. Xu Liu Liu

44
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,520
would you be willing to

45
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:47,480
Don't say it!

46
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,200
I know.

47
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,760
walk with me to the next stage of life?

48
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:50,600
You can't.

49
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:51,720
Don't say it anymore.

50
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:53,080
Look over there.

51
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:59,200
Let me play my idol's new song for you.

52
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:27,920
Bro Chen.

53
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,520
The contracts for that land on Yingchun Road,

54
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,520
most of them are signed.

55
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,720
The rest are residents of over a decade.

56
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,040
We haven't discussed the price yet.

57
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:36,600
What do you think?

58
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:40,720
Go talk to them.

59
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,880
You decide the price for the others.

60
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:42,880
As for Daji Agency,

61
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:43,920
let them name their price.

62
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,480
Daji Agency

63
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:35,720
Damn.

64
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,760
This new phone's camera is amazing.

65
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:42,560
Bro.

66
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,200
Do you have to scare people with that stupid mask?

67
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,240
Would your life be incomplete without scaring people?

68
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:48,760
Where is he?

69
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,160
Not wearing the mask is out of the question.

70
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,080
It's just that mine

71
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,800
is easier for people to spot.

72
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,080
It only looks scary.

73
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,280
From Sister Bai.

74
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,240
Take it.

75
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:05,440
This...

76
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,520
Yours is too outdated.

77
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:11,960
Tell him this:

78
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,680
He did Little Bai such a huge favor.

79
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,360
I haven't properly thanked him yet.

80
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:19,560
Call it wages or a bonus, whatever.

81
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,200
He has to take it.

82
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,840
Don't make me deliver it myself.

83
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:25,720
Sister Bai's exact words.

84
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:30,400
I've delivered both the message and the gift.

85
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:31,320
Take a look.

86
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,679
Let's go take photos tomorrow.

87
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,600
These are the old men in the park,

88
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,840
playing cards.

89
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,760
Why were you standing there watching them?

90
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:50,480
Why do you talk so much nonsense?

91
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,560
I was giving them some tips.

92
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,280
Lin You.

93
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:02,920
I told you, stop shooting over here.

94
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:03,480
Shoot over there.

95
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,200
It's gorgeous.

96
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:05,840
Really? Yeah.

97
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:06,960
Let's go, let's go.

98
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:11,400
I'm stuffed.

99
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,480
Even though it's a new phone,

100
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,920
you don't need to photograph everything.

101
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,600
But phones these days are really great.

102
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:28,160
I'm going to capture all of this,

103
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,400
so I can draw them into my comic later.

104
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:31,920
Fine.

105
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:32,960
Whatever you want.

106
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,360
I can't eat another bite.

107
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,080
I gotta go take some antacids.

108
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:42,760
Hello.

109
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,720
I'm with Flashbang right now.

110
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:47,720
What's up?

111
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,000
What?

112
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,440
When did this happen?

113
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,360
That's impossible.

114
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,800
She was fine just a couple of days ago.

115
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,840
You've looked everywhere?

116
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:04,240
Okay.

117
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:06,040
Then Lin You and I will go look.

118
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,760
What's wrong?

119
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:11,520
Liu Liu's missing.

120
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:17,040
Lao Wang said she took a few days off,

121
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,280
then just texted saying she's quitting.

122
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:21,040
And then she vanished.

123
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:22,120
She's not answering her phone.

124
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:23,840
There's no reason for her to quit.

125
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,000
Right.

126
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,320
For anyone else, it might be fine.

127
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,320
But the thing is, Liu Liu...

128
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:33,720
You know she has that schizophrenia thing.

129
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,520
Basically, it's hysteria.

130
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,560
Who knows what set her off this time.

131
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,120
When did you last see her?

132
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,040
A week ago.

133
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:45,960
A...

134
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,040
Then say no more.

135
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,000
Let's go find her, quick.

136
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,600
Come on.

137
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:54,840
Where do we look?

138
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,400
Liu Liu, Liu Liu!

139
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:00,680
Liu Liu, Liu Liu!

140
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:02,640
Liu Liu!

141
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,000
Hello.

142
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:13,880
Excuse me, may I ask,

143
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,160
have you seen a...

144
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:16,440
sweet, petite girl,

145
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:18,600
who goes to school around here?

146
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:19,600
Sir.

147
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,200
Do you have a photo of her?

148
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:31,320
She...

149
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,720
She wears a string of bells here.

150
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,480
And she loves mint candies.

151
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,440
Her hair is tied up... Lin You!

152
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:37,840
Excuse me.

153
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,680
Have you seen this person?

154
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:43,760
No.

155
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:44,160
No.

156
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:45,720
Haven't seen her.

157
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:47,080
Thanks, sorry to bother you.

158
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,320
Let's go.

159
00:11:58,840 --> 00:11:59,760
Any luck on your end?

160
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:05,600
Should we call the police?

161
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,320
Searching like this is getting us nowhere.

162
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,920
They won't open a case until it's been 48 hours.

163
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,040
Lin You, something's happened.

164
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:27,600
Lao Wang said it's from the kidnappers.

165
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,920
They want something he has.

166
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:38,080
This box.

167
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:39,800
I've hidden it for many years.

168
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:43,280
A lot of people used to ask about it.

169
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:44,880
I didn't expect

170
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,000
someone would still target it.

171
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,280
Uncle Wang.

172
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,280
I understand.

173
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,520
Saving her comes first.

174
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:55,960
Take it with you.

175
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,040
Bring Liu Liu back safely.

176
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,240
Kid.

177
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,280
Don't try anything reckless.

178
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,400
Be careful.

179
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:08,000
You've already been locked up once.

180
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:10,240
You can't afford any more trouble.

181
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,880
When I got out before,

182
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,080
I swore to myself

183
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,120
I'd never go back to prison again.

184
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:40,320
So,

185
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,120
I've been living carefully ever since.

186
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:45,520
But when I realized Liu Liu was missing,

187
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:47,280
I didn't even know where to look for her.

188
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:49,480
When the clerk asked me for her photo,

189
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:52,200
and I didn't even have one,

190
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:53,800
that's when I realized

191
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,120
how important some people and things are.

192
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:58,600
Uncle,

193
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:00,840
I've thought this through.

194
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,200
This time,

195
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:03,640
it's different.

196
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,760
You're here, buddy.

197
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:25,360
Come on, come on, come on.

198
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:28,360
You're the only one missing.

199
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,080
Everyone's already inside.

200
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:02,400
Lin You,

201
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,960
don't take it to heart, okay?

202
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:04,920
It's just that

203
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:06,480
after Lao Wang told us what happened,

204
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:09,000
we wanted to do something for you,

205
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,280
so we pulled this whole thing.

206
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,080
Please don't take it the wrong way.

207
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:13,920
Lin You.

208
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:15,760
I'm sorry.

209
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:18,200
We just wanted to...

210
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:24,280
Come with me.

211
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:33,760
Open it.

212
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:19,880
Relax.

213
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:22,760
And this one,

214
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,280
I picked it out for you myself.

215
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:26,760
I saw you always carrying that old sketchbook.

216
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:27,600
It's getting kind of worn out.

217
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,920
It's got character, sure,

218
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:31,320
but you gotta keep up with the times too.

219
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:33,800
I'm telling you, this thing has tons of features.

220
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:36,160
Super handy for finding drawing references.

221
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:37,560
Do you like it?

222
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:40,000
You getting used to the phone okay?

223
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:42,920
It's not much,

224
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,400
just a little something from me.

225
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:45,560
From now on,

226
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:46,640
this place is your home.

227
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,320
Just settle in and stay here.

228
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:50,520
Lin You,

229
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:54,760
I went and got this talisman just for you.

230
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:57,040
May your future

231
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,320
take a turn for the better,

232
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,600
and keep you safe and sound.

233
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,400
My talismans, you know,

234
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,440
don't always work.

235
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:05,240
But this time, I hope

236
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:06,640
it really does.

237
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:09,400
These all belong to you.

238
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:11,400
I'm giving them back now.

239
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:30,800
Actually,

240
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:34,440
I've been thinking about what to give you.

241
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,520
Thinking about how you're afraid of the dark,

242
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:40,920
I made you a crystal lamp by hand.

243
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,200
It's a little ugly, I know,

244
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:47,840
but...

245
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:51,400
if you're ever somewhere dark,

246
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,640
it can help you out,

247
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:55,720
then it should...

248
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:58,200
it should be pretty good, right?

249
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:18,720
Hey, kid.

250
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,400
Now that you know we tricked you,

251
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,840
are you still mad?

252
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:27,360
Now you finally know

253
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:29,800
what it feels like to have family, right?

254
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,600
I know it's a bit complicated.

255
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,520
Take your time to figure it out.

256
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:41,000
Liu Liu,

257
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,880
go grab that thawed lamb.

258
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:44,680
Okay.

259
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:48,600
Congrats on the new place!

260
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,520
That old man really loves keeping secrets.

261
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:54,800
My meat! My meat!

262
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,040
Don't put it on that plate!

263
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,440
Come on, roomie.

264
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:06,480
Let me show you around.

265
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:07,720
Let's go.
